    "##Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)\n",
    "1. Store data in data structures (memory) instead of storage (hard drives) because of speed\n",
    "2. Clean/format the data\n",
    "    - each row represents single object/observations\n",
    "    - each column represents an attribute/property/feature of the entry: atomic units that cannot be further decomposed\n",
    "    - numerical data as much as possible\n",
    "3. explore global properties: use scatter plots, histogram\n",
    "4. Explore group properties\n",
    "\n",
    "##Spotify Example\n",
    "- what ways to store the data:\n",
    "    - list of dictionaries > starts to get tedious\n",
    "    - 2D numpy array (matrix)\n",
    "- Both aren't ideal, which is why we use Pandas\n",
    "    \n",
    "##Pandas\n",
    "- open-source python library\n",
    "\n",
    "##Technical notes\n",
    "- once you do a git clone, you don't need to do it again. Just git pull to get the updates\n",
    "- If passing param based on index, use iloc. When passing based on label, use loc. iloc is exlusive, loc is inclusive.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
